 discourse. Written by experts from various disciplines, each chapter offers an integrative overview of theory, method, and contextual studies by focusing on a specific approach, interdisciplinary relationship, controversy, or theme in the field. Taking the discursive dimension in the production of knowledge seriously, the book also provides a critical analysis of academic practice and explores new forms of scholarly communication, including open peer-review. The collected volume will appeal to scholars and postgraduate students across a variety of disciplines, including religious studies, history of religion, sociology of religion, discourse studies, cultural studies, and area studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aReligionxStudy and teaching. 4aacademic practice. 4adiscourse research. 4areligious studies. 4asociology of knowledge. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  aDiscourse research.  aacademic practice.  areligious studies.  asociology of knowledge.1 aJohnston, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Jay, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJoy, Morny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Reiner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKippenberg, Hans G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoch, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaingueneau, Dominique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCutcheon, Russell T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRedden, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStuckrad, Kocku von, econtributor.4ct